comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
An outstanding photo of a mixed bag of AT-6s from Luke Field, Arizona. The closest aircraft is AT-6C-NT 41-32093 (c/n 88-9033) last of a small batch of 21 aircraft. After the war, it was transferred to the Turkish Air Force, where it carried the number 7248. Next in line is 41-15993, an AT-6A-NT. Next is AT-6A-NT 41-16009 and finally, 41-32261, an AT-6C-NT. Unfortunately, the other aircraft serials are hidden from view.

Doug MacPhail
